    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Thanks for the report.  It's not exactly that it ignores the grouping, but instead is falling through a fast-path, that assumes `rank()` is an aggregation - here:\r\nhttps://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/blob/2952fbd556e1bc4b5fac70c727652b5419e8e096/pandas/core/groupby.py#L4132\r\n\r\nI think a quick-fix would be to add `'rank'` to the list of whitelisted transforms here, but might need to rethink/refactor this whole dispatch a bit\r\nhttps://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/blob/2952fbd556e1bc4b5fac70c727652b5419e8e096/pandas/core/groupby.py#L345\r\n\r\nAlso xref to #15779"
